Jobs, I’ve had many. My job prior to @wsl was at @quiksilver . I was running the surf program and got to do some cool stuff. I signed @sealtooth to his first contract with @quiksilver (explained by Dane in the new series from @stab , “How Pro Surfers Get Paid!”), made a rad movie about @_clay_marzo called “Just Add Water” and along with many other things I talked @kellyslater into doing his first real East Coast tour… but we needed the Private Jet to get it done in time before his next event, the @ripcurl_usa search event in Mexico. I got the plane, we entertained thousands of people along with ourselves! The first stop, the venue said, “You take the door, we take the bar!” I said “Deal”, having no clue what it meant until the end of night when I said thank you and the owner handed me thousands of dollars in cash… this photo circulated and people weren’t so happy back at the office! Like how the hell did we let a bunch of surfers take our PJ and ball out… Well the tour was such a success that @kellyslater and I took the plane one last leg to the event in Mexico. When we got off in Mex we saw Andy Irons, he was so pissed we flew private he won the event… that’s another great story. #truestory #work #life #surf #world #stillinit #eastcoast #pj

The meaning of life… is there one specific meaning?! I don’t think there is just one. We all have purpose and place. Finding it is the hard part for most. Getting outta the head and into feeling, tapping into the flow. Like water moving around obstacles and sometimes taking things with us. Throw in a couple of kids, a partner and the rest of the worlds expectation. Finally after trying to fight for your way through it all you suddenly wake up, see things crystal clear! By no means are things perfect, they just are. Like this picture of my son and I, a moment of being present. You just can’t quantify it, yet it’s worth more then anything. “Watching the waves”. Thanks Susan for the 📸 #life #hope #see #clear #youmissouton100percentoftheopportunitiesyoudonttake

25 years ago my landlord was yelling at my roommate about the rent we owed! Which I had been paying, to my roommate. Not wanting to be evicted I paid another three months of rent to my roomate… I know I know, I should have paid the landlord. Either way I left to Hawaii for the season after paying the rent again. A few weeks later my roommate showed up in hawaii! Yup you guessed it, he used the rent money for his Hawaii vacation! I was like WTF man 🤦🏼‍♂️😂! He was like, you can have the 66’ Chevelle… I fixed it up and rolled it for 25 years. Then this last year I restored the entire car… We never got evicted, the car is still rolling and @reddogsxs and I are still friends.  #today #pch #california #66 #chevelle #chevy #westcoast #bestcoast #sunday #hadit25yrs

I don’t think you have years, months, weeks, days, hours… you have but a moment to live. Don’t let time/age kill your vibe/dreams. Don’t let your mind get in the way of them either, doubt is your mind getting in the way of your heart. The world of visual noise via media can give you doubt. Wash it away in open outdoor spaces like the mountains  or the ocean. Go alone, you come in alone, you go out alone, you are who you have. No one is coming to save you, love you, give you anything until you have done the work to receive it. BTW the work is never done… 😎#rant

In 1978 there was a knock on the door of our flat in the suburbs of London. My pops had just left to go get Chinese food as we had company over… The knock was loud and inappropriate, it was “The Bobby’s!” (English Police). As the guests tried to stash the the illegal substances they kicked in the door and raided the house. I vaguely remember standing close by the front door when my dad got close enough to the house to realize what was going on! I was held by the shirt as he was detained out front on the street… He went down hard for almost 10 years! We left the next day on a plane to Los Angeles, stayed at our Uncle Jim’s and with our God Parents Edward & Sharon until we landed in this building picture above, The Sea Castle Apts.. Rent Controlled and on the beach, $300 a month for a 2 bedroom apt.! All we had was the beach, we saw it all, death, drugs, violence and WAVES. My brother @mescalito70 and I would wait on the shoreline for people to lose their boards and we would grab them. Ride them in the whitewash until they realized we had em. That’s how I started surfing…. 🤷🏼‍♂️🙋🏼‍♂️. 📸 @santamonicahistorymuseum #life #surf #london #santamonica #seacastle #beatitkidthatsmyboard

I’ve been in pain since J Bay, July of last year. Hurt my neck, driver error of the jet ski I was on the back of. Then I got clipped by the lip at Cloudbreak, minor tear of my left MCL. Slammed on some rocks snowboarding, bruised my lower back. Then I hit the hard pack snowboarding on my already sore shoulder. Crumbed a few more times here and there… Come to think about it I’ve been in pain since 1996 when I broke my foot and they tried to cut half of it off! Dr O’Brian said, you can keep your foot but in 10 years you will be in “a lot” of arthritic pain. Well he was right, not a day has gone by since 2006 that I don’t limp in pain every morning. I think where I’m going with all this is life is full of pain. All the fun and good looking people you see on social platforms go through it. Everyone pays, there are no free rides. So don’t let a little pain get in the way of a good time… I could barley get to my feet on the wave pictured above, shoulder hurt like hell to pop up. It was worth it, still smiling. After over a month of not surfing this little wave felt as good as a perfect toob at Cloudbreak! 📸 @kingneptune1000  #paytoplay #nopainnogain #falldown #getup #keepgoing #yougotthis

Happy Easter Everyone… Wether you honor the holiday or not (I’m Jewish by blood but never practiced any religion) this is a funny one… the way I remember it one Easter our mom hadn’t really made anything or planned for it. Traditionally we had friends and food around… So I was like mom what’s up, she looked over with a cigarette in her mouth and a glass of chardonnay in hand… “Not this year, we are Jewish this Easter!” I was like come on mom, she was like… “Alright, you want Easter!” she pulled out a frozen pizza, made a cross outta the pepperoni and started a family tradition! #happyeaster #jewster #california #mom #missyoumom #santamonica #seacastleapartments #youth

I’d do it all over again too! The joy of toob time is second to none and the few months of time off I’m having now due to this surgery is payment for it all. When I was 13 I started surfing for @tcsurfboards and I met @danekealoha . He always had my back and looked after me growing up. Watching him surf backdoor and his movements were amazing… One day we ran into each other on Ke Nui rd, I was like 14 and someone had just stole some money from some friends of mine. He said not to worry, just tell em I’m coming to give you a ride to the airport and they would give it back. Dane knocked on the door, our money was returned and all was good! Love you Dane and thank you for always looking out for me. Rest in Aloha, ride forever… #legend #hawaiian #surfer #muchlove

Happy Mothers Day Mama… it’s been 10 yrs only I feel like you say hi all the time. So you must have been right when you said energy never dies. We visited and filmed in this location a few days ago with the @indoek crew. It reminded me of the time we were in this car and a guy with an AK-47 stopped us in this same parking lot (next door to shutters in SM). Asked us for all our money, Mom pulled the food stamps out and he said, “it’s cool you’re one of us!”. Pretty sure he robbed the next car behind us 😲. This wagon was so dope, it didn’t last long. Got stolen from the same lot about a week later. At least that’s what mom said, or we needed the money and she sold it. Either way thank you mom for keeping a roof over @mescalito70 and I head and cereal n milk on the table. Brother and I did the shopping, everything we could cook! Cereal, quesadillas, eggs, nestles quick, pb&js…. Fucking paradise I tell ya. #life #foodstamps #mom #rentcontrol #santamonica #diffdads #kickedoutat16 #seacastleapartments #sxs #dogtown

My favorite surf trip destination is @tavaruaislandresort . It’s hard to beat, just take a walk through these slides at a typical day there! Wake up to this kind of sunrise and have a coffee just before jumping on the first boat out to Cloudbreak! Pull up and see perfection with the sun lighting up the line up… Get a couple of toobs in the morning light and work up an appetite for breakfast. Then hang out with a legend like @jonroseman and if your lucky get a ride out to surf on his jet ski! Maybe get the wave of your life if you can muster up the courage to not paddle for the channel and stay in the pit when a ledge set comes! Then back to the boat for some water and self realization of how fucking amazing the situation is you are in… after hydration and a snack back out to get shacked again. Maybe even get an inside swinger set that you have your @gopro for and get the clip! You’ve skipped lunch and surfed for 4 hours and walk into a Tavarita and a sunset like no other… end up in the boatman’s bure for the after hours smack talk and a couple beverages with amazing humans. #life #surfing #tavarua @shadesunscreen

We grew here, you flew here… I’ve been friends with Ricky Massie @massiesurf for 40 years! He still lives in the same house in Venice as when we met. I wish I still had my old place in Santa Monica. Back in the 80’s things were different around here. Santa Monica and Venice were rival gangs which trickled down into the surf scene. Ricky was my nemesis in surf contests! We were friends but hated losing to each other. He never came to Santa Monica to surf and I wasn’t allowed to go to Venice and surf. Although one day @jboyadams got me a day pass and I surfed Venice Jetty really good! I went down there to skateboard with @oscarputdowntheknife and my bro @mescalito70 . But surfing was off limits to non locals… this is how it went, walk down with your surfboard and you where told not to surf there. If you kept going you were verbally abused by the locals. If you kept walking after that they threw rocks at you… if you thought you were tough and kept walking the physical abuse would go down and your fins got broken out of your board. I saw it so many times… man how times have changed! Some things never change though, good friends are for life! Was stoked to drop a board off for Rick today. He still rips, has an epic business and love for the homie. Im pretty sure I’m one up on heat wins too. Hahaha. So many stories, he got me my first meeting with @quiksilver and that lasted 20 years! Parties at Ricks house were scary… V13 & VSLC rollin by real slow, I never stood by the street. Venice and Santa Monica were shooting up each others schools at that time. Damn shit was real back then… #friendship #santamonica #venice #surf #80’s #rivals #40 #years #51 #frothing #rickmassie

I will never not be there for my boys… When I was 6 there was a knock on the door to our flat in London, England. My dad had just stepped out to get Chinese food a few minutes earlier. BOOM, cops kicked in the door, raided the house and found all the illegal substances that were stashed in the house. When my dad returned I was standing in the door way, he knew it was over. I watched them tackle him and take him away. He went down for 7 to 10 yrs… I visited him a year or two into it, mom n he fought over money the whole time. After he got out of jail my mom n pop were still fighting. My dad never showed back up… Years later he conveniently arrived in the south of France where I was working to see me, I was 30 years old. He acted like nothing had happen. Weirdest day of my life… there’s lots more to the story but the moral of it all is… I will always be here for my family. #family

Water from the ocean, waves created by a surf god, 5th element back drop by Abu Dhabi…Oh and I think the left is better then the right! @kellyslater @modonproperties @surfabudhabi @kswaveco have made an unbelievable combination of elements. I took this photo from the second story of the @surfabudhabi facility before I went into the water and surfed. I kept going back and looking at it over and over again mind blown. Then I paddled in the water, felt the extra ease of the ocean water and lightness it created. There was room for error on the wave yet it still had power and a heavy barrel. The transitions and contour of the wave lend to your attack on it and the toob… The toob sections don’t chase you down, they lift you up and carry you forward. You can play on the foam ball of the toob and your heart races while it happens. Who knew, what’s next, WTF! Much appreciation and honored to be able be here for the launch of something so special. Inspired watching @stephaniegilmore @caroline_markss @filipetoledo @gabrielmedina @ramziboukhiam @floresjeremy @kellyslater @charlesrsmith @raimanaworld smashing and slashing! One of my favorite things to do is make lunches for my kids before I take them to school… When I was in elementary school my brother @mescalito70 and I didn’t have much money. So we got government aid which meant food stamps and lunch tickets for school. Mom wasn’t one to make lunches and it was free food for a broke ass family. That food was horrible, prison food was better then our school slop and having to deal with the comments from the other kids about being broke was no joke. We learned to deal with it through middle school and into high school. To be honest I’m just realizing writing this I’m still dealing with it. Making lunches for my kids gives me a sense of pride and is very therapeutic for me. So to all those parents out there who make lunches for your kids, be proud and take some time to do it right. #love #parents #lunch
